# kanshi configuration
# ~/.config/kanshi/config
#
# Display hotplug profiles. kanshi watches for outputs appearing/disappearing
# and applies the FIRST profile all of whose listed outputs are connected
# (extra connected outputs are allowed). Two consequences drive the ordering
# below:
#   * ORDER MATTERS. Because matching is "all listed outputs connected" (not an
#     exact set), a profile listing fewer outputs also matches a superset state.
#     So the more-specific profiles (more outputs) MUST come first, otherwise a
#     one-output profile would shadow the dual-output ones.
#   * The single-output profiles (undocked=eDP only, clamshell=external only)
#     reference DIFFERENT outputs, so they don't shadow each other.
# This makes docking/undocking, clamshell, and a dual-head workstation "just
# work" the same way on every machine.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FILL IN YOUR OUTPUT NAMES.
#   Hyprland:  hyprctl monitors        (look at the "Monitor <NAME>" lines)
#   or:        wlr-randr                (lists each output name + modes)
# Laptop panels are usually eDP-1; external outputs are DP-1/DP-2/HDMI-A-1.
# Match on the connector name (and optionally "make model serial" for a
# specific monitor). Replace every REPLACE-ME below.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Laptop at a dock / with an external monitor to the right (two outputs) ---
# Internal panel on the left, external to its right. Adjust position by the
# internal panel's width (e.g. 1920,0 if eDP is 1920 wide). Listed first so it
# wins over `undocked` when both the panel and the external are connected.
profile docked {
    output "REPLACE-ME-eDP-1" enable mode 1920x1080 position 0,0 scale 1.0
    output "REPLACE-ME-DP-1" enable mode 2560x1440 position 1920,0 scale 1.0
}

# --- Desktop workstation with dual monitors (two outputs) ---
# For a headless workstation there's no eDP; list the two external outputs.
# Listed before the single-output profiles so a DP-1+DP-2 workstation isn't
# shadowed by `clamshell` (which lists only DP-1).
profile workstation {
    output "REPLACE-ME-DP-1" enable mode 2560x1440 position 0,0 scale 1.0
    output "REPLACE-ME-DP-2" enable mode 2560x1440 position 2560,0 scale 1.0
}

# --- Laptop, lid open, no external display (undocked, one output) ---
profile undocked {
    output "REPLACE-ME-eDP-1" enable mode 1920x1080 position 0,0 scale 1.0
}

# --- Laptop lid closed, external only (clamshell, one output) ---
# Lists only the external panel. When the lid closes, config/hypr/scripts/lid.sh
# disables the internal panel, so the connected set becomes just the external
# output and this profile applies (the two-output profiles above no longer match
# because the internal panel / second monitor is gone).
profile clamshell {
    output "REPLACE-ME-DP-1" enable mode 2560x1440 position 0,0 scale 1.0
}
